And I'm alone...

268
00:15:13,750 --> 00:15:16,708
But I'm happy to find people
who can see what I see...

269
00:15:16,791 --> 00:15:19,083
Yes, umm...

270
00:15:19,166 --> 00:15:21,041
I would mention it to people
but they would just mock me...

271
00:15:21,125 --> 00:15:24,666
This last month's been so hard
that I've contemplated suicide.

272
00:15:24,750 --> 00:15:26,583
But I've learned
that the only way

273
00:15:26,666 --> 00:15:28,541
to stay alive is to
dodge the snake.

274
00:15:29,875 --> 00:15:32,791
I think she's...
Lost her mind.

275
00:15:32,875 --> 00:15:34,208
Miss Lotto, tell me...

276
00:15:34,291 --> 00:15:36,000
You've been able to
see the abnormalities

277
00:15:36,083 --> 00:15:38,333
that are happening
here everyday?

278
00:15:38,416 --> 00:15:39,916
I have...

279
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:42,750
but it's as if, everyone else in
town has no idea it's happening.

280
00:15:42,833 --> 00:15:44,625
Please you have
to help me out...

281
00:15:44,708 --> 00:15:48,125
I can't stand this
insanity anymore!

282
00:15:48,208 --> 00:15:50,583
You saved my life from that
evil monster back there...!

283
00:15:50,666 --> 00:15:53,708
You've saved me once you can
save me again, can't you?!

284
00:15:53,791 --> 00:15:55,541
You need to calm
down, Miranda...

285
00:15:55,625 --> 00:15:58,916
We'll help, but we need
to work together on this.

286
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,500
That sounds really good.

287
00:16:00,583 --> 00:16:02,041
Something must have happened on

288
00:16:02,125 --> 00:16:04,458
the first October twenty-eighth
to trigger the repetition...

289
00:16:04,541 --> 00:16:06,458
any idea of what it could be?

290
00:16:06,541 --> 00:16:08,375
How many times do
I have to tell you people?

291
00:16:08,458 --> 00:16:11,458
It's always October
twenty-eighth here!

292
00:16:13,916 --> 00:16:15,208
What's wrong?

293
00:16:15,291 --> 00:16:17,666
Do you see those men
at the bar, Miranda...?

294
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:19,166
They're the only people
in town that have noticed

295
00:16:19,250 --> 00:16:22,541
you're different than
everyone else aside from us.

296
00:16:23,708 --> 00:16:26,416
I realize why you're the only
one this time warp affects...

297
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:29,375
and why you can see
things others cannot see.

298
00:16:29,458 --> 00:16:31,625
It's because you're the one
who's in contact with the

299
00:16:31,708 --> 00:16:34,375
Innocence that is causing
all these abnormalities...

300
00:16:34,458 --> 00:16:37,000
Which is why these
creatures are here.

301
00:16:38,458 --> 00:16:40,500
Innocence activate!

302
00:17:09,083 --> 00:17:10,208
Lenalee.

303
00:17:10,291 --> 00:17:11,833
Get Miranda to safety
while I handle this.

304
00:17:12,916 --> 00:17:13,958
Your Dark Boots are quicker

305
00:17:14,041 --> 00:17:15,625
than anything these
Akuma can muster.

306
00:17:15,708 --> 00:17:17,208
I'll meet up with you later!

307
00:17:17,291 --> 00:17:20,458
Be careful Allen!

308
00:17:21,125 --> 00:17:23,416
I'll come back to help
you as soon as I can.

309
00:17:32,791 --> 00:17:35,083
All three of these
Akumas are level Twos.

310
00:17:39,041 --> 00:17:40,833
I finally find the
person that can save me

311
00:17:40,916 --> 00:17:43,875
from this hell
and now he's gone!!

312
00:17:57,750 --> 00:18:00,458
So this is the rewinding town.

313
00:18:06,166 --> 00:18:08,083
Lero, wait, don't do this...!

314
00:18:08,166 --> 00:18:10,416
Leroleroleroooo!

315
00:18:21,458 --> 00:18:22,791
Who was that?

316
00:18:29,291 --> 00:18:32,625
And Road Kamelot makes
a stunning appearance.

317
00:18:36,958 --> 00:18:39,166
Pang Voice!

318
00:18:39,250 --> 00:18:42,125
Feels like my
head's... splitting!

319
00:19:00,708 --> 00:19:03,958
Hotter than flame its, ICE FIRE!

320
00:19:06,041 --> 00:19:07,833
If you come in
contact with it...

321
00:19:07,916 --> 00:19:10,166
Flesh rots instantly...

322
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:11,708
You wanna try it?

323
00:19:11,791 --> 00:19:14,791
Let's slice him up...!
Let me go first!

324
00:19:14,875 --> 00:19:16,000
Lets me do it...!

325
00:19:16,083 --> 00:19:17,208
It'll be funnier

326
00:19:17,291 --> 00:19:20,000
if I use my voice 'cause
his head'll explode!

327
00:19:21,750 --> 00:19:23,291
I will slice you to pieces!

328
00:19:23,375 --> 00:19:24,750
I'll make you rot!

329
00:19:24,833 --> 00:19:26,750
Your brain will be mush!

330
00:19:30,166 --> 00:19:31,750
One two three Scissors...!

331
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:33,666
One two three Rock...!

332
00:19:33,750 --> 00:19:35,416
One two three Paper...!

333
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:36,875
One two...

334
00:19:38,125 --> 00:19:39,458
You play dirty...!

335
00:19:39,541 --> 00:19:42,791
How dare you interrupt a
game of Rock, Paper, Scissors!

336
00:19:42,875 --> 00:19:44,750
Do you expect me to just
sit around and wait?

337
00:19:44,833 --> 00:19:46,458
We must crush the Exorcist!

338
00:19:46,541 --> 00:19:48,125
Crush him to death!

339
00:19:49,208 --> 00:19:50,833
Stop.

340
00:19:51,833 --> 00:19:54,625
You three are
having too much fun...

341
00:19:54,708 --> 00:19:55,875
Need I remind you

342
00:19:55,958 --> 00:19:58,500
that the mission is to
search for Innocence?

343
00:20:03,541 --> 00:20:05,291
Return.

344
00:20:08,458 --> 00:20:09,958
What just happened?

345
00:20:19,416 --> 00:20:21,000
Where'd they go?

346
00:20:21,083 --> 00:20:23,833
That's... a good... question...

347
00:20:23,916 --> 00:20:25,750
There was a big booming
voice in the sky...

348
00:20:25,833 --> 00:20:27,500
and then they were gone.

349
00:20:27,583 --> 00:20:29,125
A voice?

350
00:20:41,791 --> 00:20:45,083
So you wanted to
speak with us, Road?

351
00:20:45,708 --> 00:20:47,416
That is correct...

352
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:51,375
Never go behind my back and
have all the fun without me!

353
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:52,625
The boy...

354
00:20:52,708 --> 00:20:55,791
He's the one who carries
the eye of the cursed...

355
00:20:55,875 --> 00:21:00,375
It makes me wonder what approach
I should take in his death.

356
00:22:38,666 --> 00:22:41,333
Picking up on the scent
of the nearby Innocence,

357
00:22:41,416 --> 00:22:44,041
the mysterious young
girl Road arrives

358
00:22:44,125 --> 00:22:47,625
in the Rewinding Town
to stake her claim.

359
00:22:47,708 --> 00:22:49,500
On the next D. Gray-man:

360
00:22:49,583 --> 00:22:52,041
"The Bad Luck
Woman's Innocence."

361
00:22:52,125 --> 00:22:55,791
Bring forth salvation to this
tormented Akuma's soul.

